For Development Build

benefit ye hai development build pe jane se ki ,saare feature expo go app me nhi hota ,to un sb se realted project banne ke liye hame development build pe jana hi pdega so that ki natively access kr ske wo ,like camera ,haptics etc.

1.install CLI
You can use EAS Command-Line Interface (CLI) to build, update, submit, deploy or use workflows in your Expo and React Native project from a terminal window.

    npm install --global eas-cli

    COMMANDS (start with eas then following suffix)
            analytics     display or change analytics settings
            autocomplete  Display autocomplete installation instructions.
            build         start a build
            config        display project configuration (app.json + eas.json)
            credentials   manage credentials
            deploy        deploy your Expo Router web build and API Routes
            diagnostics   display environment info
            help          Display help for eas.
            init          create or link an EAS project
            login         log in with your Expo account
            logout        log out
            new           Create a new project configured with Expo Application Services (EAS)
            onboarding    continue onboarding process started on the https://expo.new website.
            open          open the project page in a web browser
            submit        submit app binary to App Store and/or Play Store
            update        publish an update group
            upload        upload a local build and generate a sharable link
            whoami        show the username you are logged in as

2.need to login
eas login
check login by--- eas whoami

3.for build run this command ---> this will create a project in expo dashboard
eas build:configure
and do yes then choose option
✅ iOS & Android: create a new standalone app from this project
then it will give u the link u can open it in browser and there u have a dashboard for that project
eas.json ---> file created in the project ,in build there is 3 options ->development,preview,production

4.run command for build
eas build --profile development --platform android

        tab for default name of app build
        then yer for key gen

5.build finish hone ke bad dashboard me install pe click krne se qr code aayega usko scan krne se phone pe download krne ka option aayega waha se aap donwlod kr ke khol skte hai

6.then when u start the application by npm stat then by pressing 's' u can switch b/w expo go to your development build app
then press a to open that in android
then aap real time me update kr skte ho and wo sb apke app me dikhega

<!-- For Preview Build -->

diff kya hai development build se --> usko share nhi kr skte apk ke jaisa but preview build ko kr skte hai share apk file ke roop me ,for qaa testing,client dmeo etc
similar to production
shareable
developemt wale me dev client ka chlte rhna jruri hai kyuki update ye sb ho rha but isme nhi hai jriro

1.go to the eas.json file and add android in preview
"preview": {
"distribution": "internal",
"android": {
"buildType": "apk"
}
},

2.run command
eas build --profile preview --platform android

How to setup production build locally ,without the help of eas build service of expo

